/**
 * @class Account
 * @brief Represents a bank account with basic operations.
 * 
 * The Account class provides functionalities to manage a bank account,
 * including depositing and withdrawing money, and retrieving account details.
 * It also supports file operations for saving and loading account information.
 * 
 * @private
 * @var int accountNumber
 *      The unique number identifying the account.
 * @var string accountHolder
 *      The name of the account holder.
 * @var double balance
 *      The current balance of the account.
 * 
 * @public
 * @fn Account()
 *      Default constructor initializing account with default values.
 * @fn Account(int accNum, string holder)
 *      Constructor initializing account with given account number and holder name.
 * @param accNum The account number.
 * @param holder The name of the account holder.
 * 
 * @fn void deposit(double amount)
 *      Deposits a specified amount into the account.
 * @param amount The amount to be deposited.
 * 
 * @fn void withdraw(double amount)
 *      Withdraws a specified amount from the account.
 * @param amount The amount to be withdrawn.
 * 
 * @fn double getBalance() const
 *      Retrieves the current balance of the account.
 * @return The current balance.
 * 
 * @fn string getAccountHolder() const
 *      Retrieves the name of the account holder.
 * @return The name of the account holder.
 * 
 * @fn int getAccountNumber() const
 *      Retrieves the account number.
 * @return The account number.
 * 
 * @fn void writeToFile(ofstream &file)
 *      Writes the account details to a file.
 * @param file The output file stream to write to.
 * 
 * @fn static Account readFromFile(ifstream &file)
 *      Reads account details from a file.
 * @param file The input file stream to read from.
 * @return An Account object with the details read from the file.
 * 
 * @fn static Account* searchAccount(int accNum)
 *      Searches for an account by account number.
 * @param accNum The account number to search for.
 * @return A pointer to the Account object if found, otherwise nullptr.
 */